- **Done**: `US-043` is implemented, `prd.json` is marked passed, `progress.txt` is appended, and the commit is `4b11f212f` on **`04-16-chore_rivetkit_to_rust`**.

- **What moved**: [`rivetkit-core` startup](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-rust/packages/rivetkit-core/src/actor/lifecycle.rs>) now runs `on_migrate` before `on_wake`, with `OnMigrateRequest { ctx, is_new }`, fatal timeout/error handling, and `on_migrate_timeout` config plumbing in [`config.rs`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-rust/packages/rivetkit-core/src/actor/config.rs>) and [`callbacks.rs`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-rust/packages/rivetkit-core/src/actor/callbacks.rs>). The typed Rust layer in [`actor.rs`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-rust/packages/rivetkit/src/actor.rs>) and [`bridge.rs`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-rust/packages/rivetkit/src/bridge.rs>) now exposes the hook too. The native TS/NAPI path in [`actor_factory.rs`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-typescript/packages/rivetkit-napi/src/actor_factory.rs>), [`native.ts`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-typescript/packages/rivetkit/src/registry/native.ts>), and [`config.ts`](</home/nathan/r5/rivetkit-typescript/packages/rivetkit/src/actor/config.ts>) now supports `onMigrate` / `onMigrateTimeout`, and `native.ts` now correctly reads runtime option fields from `definition.config.options` instead of the wrong top-level slot.

- **Checks**: `cargo test -p rivetkit-core`, `cargo test -p rivetkit`, `cargo check -p rivetkit-napi`, and `pnpm check-types` in `rivetkit-typescript/packages/rivetkit` all passed.

- **Verify**: the main thing worth eyeballing is one native TS actor that uses `onMigrate` across both first boot and wake, especially if you set a custom `options.onMigrateTimeout`.
